The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Hindustan Construction Co Ltd (HCC) will raise $100 million from overseas markets by way of issuing global depository receipts (GDRs) or other financial instruments convertible into equity shares in one or more tranches. Hindustan Construction will issue foreign currency convertible bonds, secured premium notes or equity shares through the depository receipt mechanism such as GDRs, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Centurion Bank of Punjab has received the Reserve Bank?s approval for the preferential issue of 12.9 crore shares at a price of Rs 19.25 each to Citigroup Venture Capital International Growth Partnership Mauritius Ltd and India Value Fund.

 Tulip IT Services will set up the country?s largest wireless virtual private network covering 500 cities at a cost of Rs 180 crore. ?So far, we have covered 350 cities with an investment of Rs 142 crore. We will invest another Rs 38 crore to expand it to 500 cities in the next few months,? said managing director H.S. Bedi.

 Textiles manufacturer Shree Ram Mills Ltd will issue bonus shares to its existing shareholders in the 1:5 ratio. The proposal was cleared at the extra-ordinary general meeting, the company informed the stock exchanges.

 Ispat Industries Ltd will raise $125 million through the issue of foreign currency convertible bonds. The board has approved the proposal, which is subject to other requisite approvals, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Motorola has tied up with DCM Shriram Consolidated Ltd?s Hariyali Kisan Bazaar, a chain of rural utility marts, for selling its handsets. The tie-up would offer consumers access to the latest models across various categories and price bands, Motorola said in a release.

 Color Chips Ltd, an integrated design solutions company, will raise $8 million by way of issuing either global depository receipts, foreign currency convertible bonds or other equity-linked securities in the international or domestic markets. The board has approved the proposal.

 Levis has launched its Red Loop Summer ?06 collection in Calcutta. The new range combines stylised denims in various finishes with design and glitter.

 IDBI has selected HCL Infosystems to provide the ICT infrastructure for its 100 new retail branches. The system integrated platform would address the computing, networking and office automation needs of IDBI.

